itemLabel: Victor Child Villiers, 7th Earl of Jersey
itemDescription: British banker, Conservative politician and colonial administrator (1845-1915)

wikipedia_page.main: Victor Albert George Child Villiers, 7th Earl of Jersey,  (20 March 1845 – 31 May 1915) was a British banker, Conservative politician and colonial administrator from the Villiers family. He served as Governor of New South Wales between 1891 and 1893.
